92
00:10:26,113 --> 00:10:31,051
Your wife wants that child to be safe.
Am I wrong?

93
00:10:47,535 --> 00:10:51,130
I'll take you to a path through the
woods to the north, where you can escape.

94
00:10:54,508 --> 00:10:57,375
You should go towards the path
instead of the hotel as well.

95
00:10:57,645 --> 00:11:00,307
No. I won't go anywhere.

96
00:11:01,382 --> 00:11:04,943
All right. I'll be right back.
Don't move from this spot.

97
00:11:06,120 --> 00:11:06,780
Got it?!

98
00:11:22,536 --> 00:11:23,935
It sure is quiet.

99
00:11:25,973 --> 00:11:32,345
Say... They're really not after
the lottery prize we won, are they?

100
00:11:33,247 --> 00:11:33,873
Yeah.

101
00:11:36,984 --> 00:11:40,579
Honestly. I didn't feel like I was living
for the past few days.

102
00:11:41,789 --> 00:11:43,154
There really was
something wrong with me.

103
00:11:43,691 --> 00:11:48,424
Because of that money,
I ended up buying a bunch of guns.

104
00:11:49,396 --> 00:11:51,160
Normal's what's best of all.

105
00:11:52,499 --> 00:11:53,466
Normal, huh?

106
00:11:54,468 --> 00:11:58,132
I've got to let my wife know
that we're not at fault.

107
00:11:59,306 --> 00:12:01,274
Hey, can you hear me, dear?

108
00:12:09,984 --> 00:12:10,951
Mr. Henich!

109
00:12:12,519 --> 00:12:13,486
Mr. Henich!

110
00:12:19,727 --> 00:12:21,456
M-My wife...

111
00:12:24,865 --> 00:12:25,491
Ma'am!

112
00:12:27,735 --> 00:12:29,601
I-It hurts.

113
00:12:37,811 --> 00:12:38,778
Quickly, this way!

114
00:12:40,014 --> 00:12:42,244
They're shooting at us from
the building across the street.

115
00:12:42,549 --> 00:12:43,744
Does this hotel
have a basement?

116
00:12:44,385 --> 00:12:46,149
There's a storehouse
under the kitchen.

117
00:12:49,323 --> 00:12:50,984
How are your injuries?

118
00:12:51,325 --> 00:12:52,292
What about you?

119
00:12:53,761 --> 00:12:55,160
Dad's doing this.

120
00:12:56,497 --> 00:13:00,400
Dad is going crazy because
he can't get a drink.

121
00:13:02,136 --> 00:13:03,535
No he's not, Wim.

122
00:13:04,004 --> 00:13:08,669
Dad's... Just like when he
hits me every day, Dad's...

123
00:13:08,842 --> 00:13:12,506
Do you think that your dad is the sort
of person to do this sort of thing?

124
00:13:13,314 --> 00:13:14,338
I...

125
00:13:15,149 --> 00:13:18,175
