126
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:20,887
I...

127
00:13:23,123 --> 00:13:26,821
Don't make me repeat it.
I won't let you die.

128
00:13:27,428 --> 00:13:30,557
I'm going to tie you down here
if you keep saying that.

129
00:13:31,465 --> 00:13:34,127
Stay here. I'll deal with it.

130
00:13:35,836 --> 00:13:36,803
Mr. Grimmer...

131
00:13:37,905 --> 00:13:38,872
I told you, didn't I?

132
00:13:38,972 --> 00:13:42,931
When things get tough,
the Magnificent Steiner will appear.

133
00:13:45,079 --> 00:13:46,046
Long ago...

134
00:13:46,113 --> 00:13:48,878
I've seen cases like that
during my experiments.

135
00:13:49,616 --> 00:13:54,577
By imposing an excessive amount
of stress from anger or sadness,

136
00:13:54,688 --> 00:13:57,350
a child will manifest
a different personality.

137
00:13:59,126 --> 00:14:02,323
Those children were
exceptionally violent.

138
00:14:03,130 --> 00:14:05,428
Most of them
committed suicide.

139
00:14:06,900 --> 00:14:08,698
I'm surprised you've lived
as long as you have.

140
00:14:18,512 --> 00:14:20,344
Look. I'm unarmed.

141
00:14:21,248 --> 00:14:23,546
Listen to what I have to say,
even for just a little while.

142
00:14:24,785 --> 00:14:28,244
Why are you doing this?
Who gave you your orders?

143
00:14:29,022 --> 00:14:31,957
It doesn't matter if you're people
from the old East Germany

144
00:14:32,025 --> 00:14:33,493
or if you're former
secret police.

145
00:14:33,794 --> 00:14:35,956
It doesn't matter who you are!

146
00:14:37,131 --> 00:14:39,657
I'm nobody from nowhere.

147
00:14:41,635 --> 00:14:42,261
Are you listening?

148
00:14:43,070 --> 00:14:47,871
Listen to me. Don't just follow orders,
but think with your heart.

149
00:14:48,709 --> 00:14:53,078
Think with your heart
about what you're doing.

150
00:14:54,782 --> 00:14:55,749
Can you do that?

151
00:14:57,885 --> 00:14:58,477
You can...

152
00:14:59,586 --> 00:15:00,781
What are you doing?

153
00:15:02,890 --> 00:15:05,882
I was so scared!
I came all this way by myself.

154
00:15:06,693 --> 00:15:09,094
I'm so glad that you're here.

155
00:15:10,497 --> 00:15:11,123
Huh?

156
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:28,278
<i>The Magnificent Steiner!</i>

157
00:15:29,950 --> 00:15:30,917
<i>Hey everyone!</i>

158
00:15:30,984 --> 00:15:35,046
I watched it so fervently each day,
sitting so close to the TV...

159
00:15:36,023 --> 00:15:38,048
But I have no memory of
watching the last episode.

160
00:15:38,125 --> 00:15:39,524
<i>Call out my name!</i>

161
00:15:42,963 --> 00:15:44,089
<i>Come on. Let's go.</i>

162
00:15:44,231 --> 00:15:45,255
<i>N-No.</i>

163
00:15:45,766 --> 00:15:47,791
<i>No. No.</i>

164
00:15:48,669 --> 00:15:51,468
<i>No!</i>

165
00:15:54,541 --> 00:15:58,239
<i>I wonder if the main character,
the weak young man,</i>

166
00:15:58,312 --> 00:16:04,115
<i>realized that he turned into the
Magnificent Steiner when he got angry.</i>

167
00:16:06,487 --> 00:16:10,754
<i>I wonder if that young man
found happiness.</i>

168
00:16:17,331 --> 00:16:18,526
<i>That young man...</i>

169
00:16:23,237 --> 00:16:26,537
<i>That young man
becomes happy.</i>

170
00:16:36,517 --> 00:16:37,484
It's just a little further.

171
00:16:37,985 --> 00:16:40,181
Just a little further and
we'll be out of the forest.

172
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:42,448
You're from Ruhenheim,
aren't you?

173
00:16:46,226 --> 00:16:47,193
Who are you?

174
00:16:47,661 --> 00:16:49,425
Something's happening
in the town, right?

175
00:16:50,430 --> 00:16:53,092
People came into
the town with weapons.

176
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:55,329
Everyone in town began
killing each other.

177
00:16:56,837 --> 00:16:58,066
Are you with them?

178
00:16:58,472 --> 00:17:00,941
Calm down.
We're on your side.

179
00:17:01,808 --> 00:17:05,767
Did you see an Asian man...
a Japanese man with long hair?

180
00:17:06,380 --> 00:17:08,576
Do you know him?

181
00:17:09,116 --> 00:17:10,140
So you do know him!

182
00:17:10,484 --> 00:17:14,182
Y-Yeah. He was desperately trying
to help these children get away.

183
00:17:14,821 --> 00:17:17,552
Right now, he's staying in
the town trying to save people.

184
00:17:18,425 --> 00:17:21,087
When we split up,
he mentioned the Hotel Versteck.

185
00:17:22,129 --> 00:17:23,096
Oh, Nina!

186
00:17:24,164 --> 00:17:26,826
I left my car right outside
the path through the woods.

187
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:29,936
Use that car to transport
the injured and the sick.

188
00:17:30,504 --> 00:17:33,201
And contact the police
as soon as possible.

189
00:17:33,440 --> 00:17:35,932
A-Are you planning on
going to the town?

190
00:17:36,310 --> 00:17:38,472
You shouldn't do that.
You'll get killed!

191
00:17:38,812 --> 00:17:42,442
Tenma's...
that Asian man is my friend.

192
00:17:43,317 --> 00:17:46,651
I'm going to save him.
Contact the police immediately!

193
00:17:57,497 --> 00:17:58,760
Hotel Versteck...

194
00:18:30,464 --> 00:18:31,488
Mr. Grimmer...

195
00:18:34,801 --> 00:18:39,136
Hey. I knew you'd come,
Dr. Tenma.

196
00:18:40,474 --> 00:18:45,878
Two in the neighboring building...
one on the floor below this one...

197
00:18:45,946 --> 00:18:47,004
and one here.

198
00:18:48,248 --> 00:18:49,807
I got a total of four of them.

199
00:18:51,318 --> 00:18:53,980
The Magnificent Steiner appeared,
didn't he?

200
00:18:55,288 --> 00:18:58,019
No. He didn't come.

201
00:18:59,259 --> 00:19:05,289
I did it on my own.
I did it in a fit of anger.

202
00:19:07,401 --> 00:19:08,732
Anyway, those wounds...

203
00:19:09,136 --> 00:19:10,103
Oh yeah...

204
00:19:11,004 --> 00:19:12,233
So I don't forget...

205
00:19:13,674 --> 00:19:17,907
Here. It's a letter.
I got it from Inspector Lunge.

206
00:19:19,146 --> 00:19:21,478
He found it in
the Red Rose Mansion.

207
00:19:23,250 --> 00:19:28,848
Help him. He headed to
the Hotel Bergbach by himself.

208
00:19:30,023 --> 00:19:31,218
Before I do that, you...

209
00:19:31,625 --> 00:19:32,592
I'm fine.

210
00:19:33,593 --> 00:19:36,358
Let me rest.. .for a while.

211
00:19:42,436 --> 00:19:43,460
Let me introduce you.

212
00:19:44,538 --> 00:19:46,438
This is. ..Franz Bonaparta.

213
00:19:48,542 --> 00:19:49,634
Mr. Grimmer...

214
00:19:52,746 --> 00:19:54,976
It's all right, Wim.

215
00:20:01,188 --> 00:20:03,054
It's been raining a lot.

216
00:20:04,424 --> 00:20:10,557
This area is nice when it's sunny. ..
don't you think, Dr. Tenma?

217
00:20:12,199 --> 00:20:12,825
Yes.

218
00:20:13,467 --> 00:20:18,530
When it gets sunny again,
let's have a picnic with Wim here.

219
00:20:20,173 --> 00:20:20,799
Yeah.

220
00:20:21,608 --> 00:20:25,511
We'll have good wine...
and good cheese.

221
00:20:27,380 --> 00:20:28,006
Yeah.

222
00:20:34,521 --> 00:20:35,488
I'm sad.

223
00:20:37,390 --> 00:20:39,882
I'm not sad
because I'm going to die.

224
00:20:41,995 --> 00:20:47,798
Right now,
I'm sad because my son died.

225
00:20:49,803 --> 00:20:53,137
You can't make
people's feelings go away.

226
00:20:55,408 --> 00:21:01,006
My emotions were
lost somewhere.

227
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:10,581
It's as if I had received a letter that
had been sent to me decades ago.

228
00:21:14,461 --> 00:21:18,091
So this is true sadness...

229
00:21:19,633 --> 00:21:23,592
So this is happiness...

230
00:21:32,012 --> 00:21:36,040
The last episode of
The Magnificent Steiner...

231
00:21:37,717 --> 00:21:44,623
He probably turned back
into a human.

232
00:21:56,937 --> 00:21:57,927
Mr. Grimmer?

233
00:21:59,272 --> 00:22:00,296
Mr. Grimmer?

234
00:22:01,741 --> 00:22:02,799
Mr. Grimmer!

235
00:22:04,711 --> 00:22:06,873
Mr. Grimmer!

236
00:22:17,891 --> 00:22:18,881
I...

